canonical_structure.name: UBX-LOG-RETRIEVE
canonical_structure.description: Request log data. Log entries are returned in chronological order.

fields.name: startNumber
fields.description: Index of first log entry to be transferred.

fields.name: entryCount
fields.description: Number of log entries to transfer.

issues: Granularity mismatch: Merged 'version' (U1) and 'reserved' (3 bytes) into a single 'reserved0' (U4) field at offset 8. The byte layout is compatible but lacks field definition precision.
Major Error: Missing functional field 'entryCount' at offset 4.
Incorrectly defined offset 4 as an 8-byte reserved block, obscuring both 'entryCount' and 'version'.
Minor naming inconsistency: Reserved field named 'reserved1' instead of 'reserved0'.

adjudication.reasoning: There is strong consensus (9 out of 11 sources, spanning generations from M8 to M10) on the 12-byte structure containing `startNumber` (U4), `entryCount` (U4), `version` (U1), and `reserved` (3 bytes). Extraction 4 simplifies the last 4 bytes into a single U4 reserved field, which is structurally compatible but loses the version definition. Extraction 5 contains a critical error where it swallows the `entryCount` field into a large reserved block, which contradicts all other protocol versions and functionality requirements.
